1. Definitions

"Software" means the Edge Workspace Manager source code, documentation,
executable files, installers, update manifests, and other materials distributed
with this License.

"Licensor" means Thanakhan Pariput.

"Official Binary" means an executable, installer, ZIP package, update
manifest, or other compiled release published through an Official Distribution
Channel controlled or expressly authorized by the Licensor.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, adaptation, fork, translation,
integration, or other work based substantially on the Software or its source
code.

"Official Distribution Channel" means the GitHub Releases page of
abnkei/edge-workspace-manager, a Microsoft Store listing published by the
Licensor, a website or server controlled by the Licensor, or another channel
expressly authorized in writing by the Licensor.

"Primary Software Value" means that a product or service is purchased mainly
to obtain access to, operation of, support for, or functionality derived from
the Software. Indicators include marketing the Software's features as a main
service benefit, pricing by Software users, Workspaces, Tabs, installations, or
support levels, or a material loss of the service's value if the Software were
removed. Merely using the Software as an incidental tool within a broader RPA,
infrastructure, automation, security, integration, or business-operations
service does not by itself create Primary Software Value.

"Contribution" means copyrightable source code, documentation, tests, or other
material intentionally submitted for inclusion in the Software.

